      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MR TADASHI (6) in career-best form with the two dominant wins over this track and trip. Has a distinct liking for the heavy tracks after stalking the speed for a dominant win here on June 21. Can carry the extra weight and prove hard to stop. REEL CRYSTAL (7) dour filly who races best on rain-affected tracks. Shouldered the 59kg for a courageous win over 2145m at Goulburn in easier grade. Can sit just off the speed and figure prominently. QUAMBY (1) was two months between runs when he tackled city class with a fading seventh over 1800m at Caulfield Heath in BM70 grade. Anchored with the 64.5kg and can run into the minor money. ANULFA (5) found the 1600m too short first-up with a plugging fifth at Gosford on the heavy surface. Key jockey change and look for a better showing.",
